It was a check written in a very bold hand with a signature about a half inch high. When the society was formed about a year ago, Goodell said: We sent an invitation to Lucille Ball to be a member, and she sent back a check for $500 for a life membership. Garifi, community relations director for the community college, said the honorary degree will be awarded posthumously. On May 20, Miss Ball was to receive an honorary degree from the college and had planned to return to Jamestown, now a city of about 40000. 